metadata.name: WAVE TONES #30
metadata.description:
The concept of "WAVE TONES" is taken from the previous release "DISCRETEw" in the chain, where the nature of waves interpolation demonstrates process of discretizing a constant single-tone wave into multiple moving block elements at different scales.

In the next "WAVE TONES" generation the algorithm is exploring Tones of  Wave and is connecting sound harmony and visual art in one by rescaling the geometry of waves according to harmonic frequencies of 3-tones for single wave.

The tuned Waves are representing result Tones visually by overlapping groups of Waving Tones in one geometric pattern.  

Separate composition in sound is based on random chords from another addition scales of sounding frequencies generated by independent sinewave generators. 

Few groups of overlapping visual tones of waves are combined with related sonic concept in sounding frequencies and the result composition is forming audio visual experience of "WAVE TONES"

UI features: 
press "g" to record 360 frames loop gif animation at the current window size. 
press "s" to save current static frame in png image.

metadata.name: Mi  #71
metadata.description:
"Mi" for Mimicry
By imitating the colours and shapes of nature, the project seeks to create a digital version of reality that is both familiar and surreal. The resulting landscapes are at once recognizable and otherworldly, inviting viewers to explore the boundaries between the natural and the artificial.

"Mi" as a musical note
"Mi" synthesises a noise function to create dramatic landscapes, much like a musician who manipulates the frequencies of a musical composition.

"Mi" for Mile/Minute
Creating art is a journey that can take us down unexpected paths, and "Mi" embraces the idea of exploration and experimentation.

Tech Note
Please use the quality settings (press "Q") to generate a higher quality image. The project has been optimised for maximum performance, so it can be rendered on older machines. You can also adjust the resolution to your liking by pressing "R".

Press "S" to save the image.

The code has been tested on my old MacBook and various Windows machines. For best results, please use a modern Chromium-based browser, and ensure that your browser supports WebGL 2.


superbialux

metadata.name: Equilibrium #24
metadata.description: Equilibrium shows the algorithm in its search for balance in color and composition. It symbolizes how, at its core, generative art itself is the act of balancing constraints and freedom, consistency and variation, predictability and surprise. Based on empirical data, all mints should eventually converge to a stable state, though this is not guaranteed mathematically. Implemented in 5121 hand-crafted characters of JS code. Forever limited to 100 unique editions living on the Tezos blockchain. London - December 2021.

metadata.name: My essence, My Connectible #85
metadata.description:
The 'My essence, My Connectible' collection expresses the essence of web3 human beings when we define ourselves not through a self-portrait but display our inner perception of our personality.

My Connectible is My Essence, it is as alive as I am, it is always in motion.

Features:

⚡ 17 color skins /themes/: Сolor Sketch, X-Ray, Black Marble, Сoral, Pure Color, Marine, Vintage, Scheme, Chalks, Reverse, Jazz, Copper, Ball Pen, Grunge, Neon, Dusted Truffle, Violet. Each theme contains 1-7 palettes.

⚡ Two background textures: either dots or lines.

⚡ Three types of entities: сircles, triangles, and rhombuses. They have a core... or they don't.

⚡ Dynamic number of blocks: 3x3, 4x4, 5x5, 6x6, 7x7.

Animation saving works in test mode (Chrome only): press 'open live' button, press 'S', wait 10-15 seconds. The saved GIF will open in a pop-up window or a new tab.

metadata.name: Lookouts #36
metadata.description:
Lookouts is a generative illustration done 100% in code using p5js. Inspired by my love for travel and minimalist design, this collection is built based on custom shapes filled with solid colors & limited texture.

The accompanying fxtext article (in ‘Mentions’ below) shares more details about the inspiration and development process of this project.

Lookouts renders as a fixed resolution output (2000 x 1666px). Controls (in live view): 
Press [4] to render at 4000 x 3333px
Press [8] to render at 8000 x 6666px
Press [s] to save the current view (default or higher resolution image)

metadata.name: Skravert #193
metadata.description:
‘Skravert’ - Norwegian, verb, past tense. ‘The act of filling an area with lines; to shade an area’.

Skravert is a series of 320 sketches, each capturing the texture and feel of a material residing somewhere between cardboard and woolen rugs. The project is centred around rectangle subdivision and a line drawing algorithm, giving each piece its own unique expression when combined with a selection of 28 different color  palettes.  

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2021

metadata.name: circular flow #36
metadata.description:
this animated artwork explores the concept of obsession, where thoughts endlessly loop and repeat, spiraling into themselves with relentless intensity.
a sequence begins, persists, and returns to itself, like a cycle that can't be broken.
it represents the mind fixating on a singular idea, where every iteration builds upon the last, yet never reaches resolution.

the work embodies the compulsion to revisit, rework, and refine — to return to the same thought or action repeatedly, despite the absence of closure.
it reflects the ceaseless pull of obsession, where focus narrows to a single point, and every detail becomes magnified.
the energy of obsession is both captivating and exhausting, driving the work forward while tethering it in place.

as the artwork unfolds, it reveals the hypnotic nature of entrapment, drawing the viewer into a labyrinth of endless variations.

the final form is intricate, dense, and complex, a structure that seems to go nowhere and everywhere at once.
this work does not aim to resolve the obsession—it immerses the viewer in the endless loop, allowing them to feel the pull of obsession, the tension of its constant reappearance, and the overwhelming power it holds.

metadata.description:
Tender is a curatorial platform and community that helps bring incredible works of generative art to discerning collectors.

Holding a TENDER Pass enables enriched benefits and experiences within the Tender ecosystem. Every Pass minted and resold directly enables Tender to continue creating the platform and experiences that serve this mission.

metadata.name: NAZCA #65
metadata.description:
Real time animation (WebGL)
Variable dimension
2022

Nazca is a group of living glyphs made in the soil of the GPU. There are 17 figures that get combined and mixed over three layers. The figures vary in complexity but are generally created with vertical and horizontal lines only. Figures have at least one seed, some even have a seed per path. A seed is an oscillating pixel that can be compared to a square wave oscillator of audio synthesis and is usually followed by a path or a set of paths. The purpose of the paths is to send the pixels along the lines to make the figures visible through movement and to create a reduction to pure animation.

👽 Kim Asendorf
